---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Jenny K Walsh — One Page Checkout">
  <div class="case-study">

    <div class="case-study-header">
      <p class="label">Shopify &nbsp;·&nbsp; Case study</p>
      <h1>One Page Checkout</h1>
      <p class="role">Senior Product Designer</p>
      <p class="subtitle">Redesigning Shopify's flagship product for real-world complexity</p>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-image">
      <div class="image-placeholder hero-placeholder">
        <span>One Page Checkout on desktop and mobile, solid background, with components scattered around</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content">

      <section class="section first-section">
        <h2>Context</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>One Page Checkout was Shopify's most ambitious redesign of its flagship product, collapsing a three-step checkout into a single page.</p>
          <p>At Shopify's scale, this is not just a UI problem. Over 18% of global e-commerce GMV flows through Checkout, and every merchant customizes it differently.</p>
          <p>The initial design defined a simplified "green path." My role was to take that foundation and make it work across the full reality of Shopify. Every permutation, every edge case, every downstream dependency.</p>
          <blockquote class="pullquote">The green path was simple. The reality was not.</blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder section-image">
          <span>Side-by-side comparison of legacy 3-step checkout vs One Page Checkout</span>
          <span class="placeholder-sub">3 page loads → 1 &nbsp;&nbsp;·&nbsp;&nbsp; Reduced steps</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>My role</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>The initial design solved the happy path. I owned everything that came after: the full system, the edge cases, the permutations, the rollout. The work that made the vision shippable.</p>
          <ul class="role-list">
            <li>Designed for every dimension of checkout complexity</li>
            <li>Built the cross-team source of truth for all checkout permutations</li>
            <li>Contributed permutation specs to the Checkout Design System</li>
            <li>Led alignment across design, product, and engineering</li>
            <li>Partnered with engineering through build</li>
            <li>Owned the merchant-facing rollout experience</li>
          </ul>
          <blockquote class="pullquote">I took the simplified vision and made it hold. Across every merchant, every edge case, every condition Shopify supports.</blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder section-image">
          <span>Step-and-repeat grid of merchant checkouts across many different branding styles</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>The reality of checkout</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>Checkout is not one flow. It is thousands of flows.</p>
          <p>Different buyers, regions, payment methods, shipping models, custom fields, extensions. Each one introduces new states, constraints, and failure points.</p>
          <p>At this scale, edge cases are not edges. They are the product.</p>
          <p>The challenge was not just to simplify checkout, but to ensure that simplification held under every condition Shopify supports.</p>
          <blockquote class="pullquote">At Shopify's scale, edge cases aren't edge cases. They're the product.</blockquote>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="content">

      <div class="what-i-did-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">What I did</h2>
      </div>

      <section class="section subsection">
        <h2>Covered the full system</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>Extended the one-page framework beyond the happy path to cover every real-world scenario Shopify supports.</p>
          <ul class="permutation-grid">
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Product types</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Digital, physical, free, and subscription products, each with distinct checkout requirements</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Delivery options</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Shipping, pickup in store, local pickup, and ship to pickup points</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Inventory states</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Out of stock, quantity changes, price changes, and products unavailable in certain markets</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Error states</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Inline, section-level, and page-level errors, each requiring distinct handling and hierarchy</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Payment types</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Credit cards, express checkout wallets, cash on delivery, and local payment methods</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Guest checkout</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Unauthenticated buyer flows with no saved information to rely on</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Customer accounts</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Authenticated flows with prefilled addresses, saved payment methods, and order history</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Shop Pay integration</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Seamless handoff to Shop Pay, a separate product designed by a different team, requiring careful coordination</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="perm-label">Merchant configurations</span>
              <span class="perm-desc">Tipping, extensions, and the full range of how merchants set up their store</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <blockquote class="pullquote">Every new scenario wasn't an exception. It was another requirement the system had to absorb.</blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder section-image">
          <span>Hero image of specific checkout components laid out across different states and variants</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section subsection no-divider">
        <h2>Built the source of truth</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>Created a living artifact that mapped every permutation of checkout. This became the shared reference point across teams and is still used to align design and engineering decisions.</p>
          <blockquote class="pullquote">The artifact became the place where design and engineering stopped guessing.</blockquote>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section subsection no-divider">
        <h2>Led alignment across teams</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>Ran working sessions and reviews with design, product, and engineering leadership. Kept multiple teams moving toward a single, coherent system.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section subsection no-divider">
        <h2>Partnered through build</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>Worked directly with engineers during implementation. Solved edge cases as they emerged and ensured what shipped matched the intent of the system.</p>
          <blockquote class="pullquote">Design didn't hand off. It stayed in the room until it worked.</blockquote>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section subsection no-divider">
        <h2>Designed the rollout</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>We made a deliberate decision to run the experiment at the shop grain. No merchant's buyers would ever see two different checkout experiences on the same store. It was the right call for merchants, and a harder one for us, requiring careful coordination across design, PM, engineering, and data to ensure we could still measure success accurately.</p>
          <p>I solely owned the merchant-facing side of this. Merchants had been asking for One Page Checkout for years, and there was real appetite to get in early. I designed the opt-in experience in the admin: how merchants discovered it, how they enrolled, and how we communicated that early access was optional now but universal adoption was coming.</p>
          <p>That meant designing the full arc: opt-in, opt-out, phased messaging, in a way that gave merchants a genuine sense of control while being honest about where things were headed.</p>
          <blockquote class="pullquote">The hardest part wasn't designing the system. It was getting millions of merchants to move to it, on their terms, then on ours.</blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder section-image">
          <span>Admin opt-in flow for One Page Checkout early access</span>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="content content-lower">

      <section class="section outcome">
        <h2>Outcomes</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <blockquote class="pullquote outcome-pullquote">Simplification only matters if it holds at scale.</blockquote>
          <div class="metrics">
            <h3>Metrics</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>66% reduction in page loads</li>
              <li>9% fewer form fields</li>
              <li>66% reduction in clicks</li>
              <li>Optimized for mobile, which represents the majority of traffic</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="impact">
            <h3>Impact</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Delivered a checkout system that supports Shopify's full range of merchant use cases</li>
              <li>Established a living system artifact that continues to guide development</li>
              <li>Enabled a successful rollout across millions of merchants</li>
              <li>Contributed to maintaining Shopify's position as the highest converting checkout on the internet</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="closing">
        <blockquote class="pullquote closing-quote">This wasn't just a redesign. It was making a global system behave.</blockquote>
        <div class="image-placeholder section-image closing-image">
          <span>Step-and-repeat grid of desktop checkout screens across different merchant storefronts</span>
        </div>
        <div class="closing-text">
          <p>The vision was a simpler checkout. My work was making that simplicity hold up everywhere Shopify operates, across millions of merchants, every buyer state, and the full complexity of global commerce.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="back-link">
        <a href="/work">← All work</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .case-study {
    padding-bottom: 8rem;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  .case-study-header {
    padding: 180px 3rem 3rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
  }

  .label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .role {
    display: inline-block;
    align-self: flex-start;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    background: var(--black);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--black);
    opacity: 0.7;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 1200px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .first-section {
    border-top: none;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.2;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .section-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* "What I did" header */
  .what-i-did-header {
    padding: 4rem 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .subsection {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .no-divider {
    border-top: none;
  }

  .what-i-did-header + .subsection {
    border-top: none;
  }

  .subsection h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .hero-placeholder {
    padding: 8rem 2rem;
    margin: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    border-left: none;
    border-right: none;
  }

  /* Permutation tags */
  .permutations-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .permutation-grid {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .permutation-grid li {
    background: var(--white);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .permutation-grid li::before {
    display: none;
  }

  .perm-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    background: #F6FF00;
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .perm-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: rgba(0,0,0,0.65);
  }

  /* Pullquotes */
  .pullquote {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--black);
    border-left: 3px solid #F6FF00;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  /* Role list */
  .role-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .role-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .role-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.65em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    background: #F6FF00;
  }

  /* Image placeholders */
  .image-placeholder {
    background: #f5f5f5;
    border: 1px dashed rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
  }

  /* Full-width images: span both grid columns and bleed to content edge */
  .section > .section-image {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    margin: 0 -3rem -4rem;
    border-radius: 0;
    border-left: none;
    border-right: none;
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* Closing image */
  .closing > .section-image {
    margin-left: -3rem;
    margin-right: -3rem;
    border-radius: 0;
    border-left: none;
    border-right: none;
  }

  .image-placeholder span {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .placeholder-sub {
    font-size: 0.8rem !important;
    font-weight: 700 !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .image-break {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
  }

  .image-break img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  /* Outcome section */
  .outcome {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border-top: none;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .outcome h2 {
    color: #F6FF00;
  }

  .outcome .section-body {
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .outcome-pullquote {
    border-left-color: #F6FF00;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  /* Metrics + Impact sub-sections within outcome */
  .metrics,
  .impact {
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .metrics h3,
  .impact h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #F6FF00;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .metrics ul,
  .impact ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .metrics li,
  .impact li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .metrics li::before,
  .impact li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.65em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    background: #F6FF00;
  }

  /* Closing section */
  .closing {
    padding: calc(2rem + 10px) 3rem 4rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .closing-quote {
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.5vw, 1.6rem);
    border-left-width: 4px;
  }

  .closing-image {
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
  }

  .closing-text {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Back link */
  .back-link {
    padding: 4rem 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .back-link a {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    text-decoration: none;
    background-color: #F6FF00;
    padding: 0 4px;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: box-shadow 0.1s steps(2), transform 0.1s steps(2);
  }

  .back-link a:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 6px 3px 0 #00FFFF, -6px -3px 0 #FF00FF;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .case-study-header {
      padding: 160px 1.5rem 2rem;
    }

    .content {
      padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .what-i-did-header {
      padding: 2rem 0 0;
    }

    .back-link {
      padding: 2rem 0 0;
    }

    .outcome {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      margin-left: 0;
      margin-right: 0;
      border-radius: 0;
    }

    .permutation-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .section > .section-image {
      margin: 0 0 -2rem;
    }

    .closing > .section-image {
      margin-left: -1.5rem;
      margin-right: -1.5rem;
    }

    .closing {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }
  }
</style>
